# ============================================
# 🔔 Firebase Configuration for Push Notifications
# ============================================

# Firebase Project Configuration
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID="your-firebase-project-id"
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID="your-firebase-app-id"
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY="your-firebase-api-key"
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID="your-firebase-messaging-sender-id"

# ============================================
# 📝 Instructions for Setup
# ============================================

# 1. Create a Firebase Project at https://console.firebase.google.com
#
# 2. Enable Cloud Messaging (FCM)
#
# 3. Download google-services.json (Android) and place it in:
#    /Users/user/Desktop/tawreed/tawreedApp/android/app/
#
# 4. Download GoogleService-Info.plist (iOS) and add to Xcode project
#
# 5. Fill in the values below from Firebase Console:
#    - Project Settings > General > Project ID
#    - Project Settings > General > App ID
#    - Project Settings > Service Accounts > Private Key File (parse JSON)
#
# 6. Restart Expo development server: npx expo start -c

# ============================================
# 🚀 Current Status
# ============================================

# To check current Firebase status:
# - Android: Check if google-services.json exists
# - iOS: Check if GoogleService-Info.plist is added in Xcode
# - Both: Run `npm run test` to verify configuration

# ============================================
# 📱 Testing Push Notifications
# ============================================

# After setup, test with:
# 1. Run the app on a physical device
# 2. Go to Firebase Console > Cloud Messaging > Send Test Message
# 3. Select your app and device
# 4. Click "Send test message"
# 5. You should see the notification on your device
